WEBVTT

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:10.059
<v Roberto Remedios> Hello everyone, 
welcome to the WordPress Accessibility Day 2020.

00:00:10.059 --> 00:00:16.400
My name is Roberto Remedios. 
I live in San Jose, Costa Rica.

00:00:17.059 --> 00:00:20.400
<v Raghavendra Satish> Hello everyone.

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:26.610
<v Roberto> I'm user experience 
and a user interface designer. 

00:00:28.610 --> 00:00:34.470
I'm also an advocate to accessibility. 

00:00:34.470 --> 00:00:38.070
I have been working on accessibility 
a couple of years already.

00:00:38.470 --> 00:00:44.070
I fund, with a couple of friends, 
a local meetup group here 

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:48.070
and a Facebook group, 
mostly material in Spanish.

00:00:48.070 --> 00:00:53.710
My native language is Spanish, 
so if you know the accent sorry.

00:00:58.710 --> 00:01:02.960
The next talk that we're gonna listen

00:01:02.960 --> 00:01:07.680
is Gutenberg Accessibility, 
A Screen Reader User's Perspective.

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:15.119
The speaker will be Raghavendra Satish.

00:01:15.119 --> 00:01:20.450
Raghavendra is a digital accessibility evangelist.

00:01:20.119 --> 00:01:25.450
He works at the Deque Systems 
as a Senior Accessibility Consultant.

00:01:25.450 --> 00:01:33.939
He's always breaking [tackling]
web and mobile accessibility challenges.

00:01:33.939 --> 00:01:37.130
He's author of an accessibility blog,

00:01:37.130 --> 00:01:42.709
and is galvanizing the adoption of accessibility

00:01:42.709 --> 00:01:49.709
by inspiring the local tech community
with meetups and mentorships. 

00:01:49.709 --> 00:01:55.729
He propelled his thoughts 
by founding HelloA11Y, 

00:01:55.729 --> 00:02:02.279
a community [of] accessibility professionals.

00:02:02.279 --> 00:02:05.939
When he's away from his computer 

00:02:05.939 --> 00:02:11.939
we can find Raghava
at the local cafes and restaurants,

00:02:11.939 --> 00:02:17.030
sampling cuisine, attending local meetups, 

00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:20.620
these audiobooks or writing on his personal blog. 

00:02:24.620 --> 00:02:31.610
He also helped small business 
and individuals [with]

00:02:31.610 --> 00:02:38.060
digital training, marketing,
and SEO consulting. 

00:02:38.060 --> 00:02:43.060
He has been building websites 
and doing SEO consulting

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:48.580
for more than 14 years. 

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:53.580
So please, let's welcome Raghavendra. 
Thank you.

00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:57.800
<v Raghavendra> Thank you, Roberto.
Am I audible now?

00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:02.150
<v Roberto> You have your presentation right
now and your presentation is full screen,

00:03:02.150 --> 00:03:04.240
so you're ready to go.

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:10.570
<v Raghavendra> Hi everyone. 
Welcome to WordPress Accessibility Day 2020. 

00:03:10.570 --> 00:03:15.570
I'm excited to be here to share
my views on Gutenberg Accessibility.

00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:17.130
I'm a person with visual disability.

00:03:17.130 --> 00:03:21.490
My name is Raghavendra 

00:03:21.490 --> 00:03:25.490
and I'll be sharing some of my insights 
as a person with disability who is using Gutenberg.

00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:31.190
I've been building websites on WordPress 
for about 12 years now.

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:36.600
Just because it's easy 
to build websites on WordPress. 

00:03:36.600 --> 00:03:40.600
It's like I fell in love 
with WordPress.

00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:42.460
I worked with Joomla, Drupal, 

00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:47.460
and other CMS, 
content management systems,

00:03:48.460 --> 00:03:50.690
but I fell in love with WordPress 
about 12 years back 

00:03:50.690 --> 00:03:54.690
when I initially 
started with web.

00:03:58.420 --> 00:04:03.770
as Roberto introduced, I work with Deque Systems
as a Senior Accessibility Consultant. 

00:04:03.770 --> 00:04:09.190
I also run a meetup community 
called HelloA11y, HelloA11y.com,

00:04:09.190 --> 00:04:15.190
and we do a lot of meetups 
and small conferences 

00:04:15.190 --> 00:04:19.600
here in India to nurture accessibility

00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:25.540
and promote accessibility 
within the tech community.

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:29.450
Today's agenda is going to be about 
Gutenberg Accessibility. 

00:04:29.450 --> 00:04:35.450
We all know that Gutenberg
is a rich editor in WordPress

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:39.390
and I'll be taking you through 

00:04:39.390 --> 00:04:42.390
some of the accessibility and
usability challenges,

00:04:42.390 --> 00:04:45.730
like how people with screen readers and

00:04:45.730 --> 00:04:48.450
disabilities perceive content

00:04:48.450 --> 00:04:53.450
and some of my insights 
on how I work with Gutenberg

00:04:53.450 --> 00:04:59.020
and basically how I work with content
for my blogs that I run. 

00:04:59.020 --> 00:05:01.020
I run about 5–6 blogs actively.

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:11.840
A few years back I used to own and run

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:14.840
more than 20–25 blogs.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:19.000
I'm into affiliate marketing, 
search optimization also,

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:24.070
so that's where all my experience 
working with content editing 

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:27.070
and content management comes.

00:05:29.110 --> 00:05:35.590
Today's agenda is going to be why 
Gutenberg needs a learning curve. 

00:05:35.590 --> 00:05:41.051
Even as a power screen reader user, 
when I mean a power screen reader user,

00:05:41.051 --> 00:05:46.310
I've been using screen reader 
for about 15 years now since 2005, 2006. 

00:05:46.310 --> 00:05:48.310
I'm not born blind. 

00:05:48.310 --> 00:05:53.310
I became blind at a later
stage in my life

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:58.139
due to Retinitis Pigmentosa, 
a genetical disorder. 

00:05:58.139 --> 00:06:02.560
So I've been losing my eyesight for a while 
and I've been a low vision user. 

00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:05.560
I used a screen magnification
software like Magic

00:06:05.560 --> 00:06:11.840
and then slowly I transitioned
in using screen readers full time like

00:06:11.840 --> 00:06:13.370
JAWS and NVDA,

00:06:13.370 --> 00:06:17.370
which I regularly use now as part of my

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:22.560
job and day-to-day activities on the computer.

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:25.699
So even as a person with a 
power screen reader user, 

00:06:25.699 --> 00:06:28.690
like I've been using for 15 years 
the screen reader, 

00:06:28.690 --> 00:06:32.690
even for me when I initially
started with Gutenberg, 

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:34.580
it needs a lot of learning curve 

00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:37.580
because there are no tutorials on 

00:06:37.580 --> 00:06:40.690
how to use Gutenberg 
with a screen reader.

00:06:40.690 --> 00:06:45.690
I'll be demoing some of these challenges

00:06:45.690 --> 00:06:48.620
as soon as you get to 

00:06:48.620 --> 00:06:52.620
the editing part of the post

00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:58.840
what happens really and how, what are
the challenges that I faced.

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:03.480
So how to work with Gutenberg 
using a screen reader. 

00:07:03.480 --> 00:07:05.480
We will be walking through a demo

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:08.920
and the usability challenges

00:07:08.920 --> 00:07:10.920
and then the some of 
the accessibility challenges

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:13.340
that I have seen in Gutenberg.

00:07:16.340 --> 00:07:18.020
What is Gutenberg?

00:07:18.020 --> 00:07:22.020
Gutenberg is introduced in WordPress 5.0. 

00:07:22.020 --> 00:07:26.020
It is a rich editor 
and, in my perspective,

00:07:26.020 --> 00:07:29.979
what I have seen is that you 

00:07:29.979 --> 00:07:32.979
basically being used to 
create rich content.

00:07:32.979 --> 00:07:35.160
When I say rich content, 
it's not just headings, lists, paragraphs.

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:39.360
Great design also. 
The topography, all the layouts – 

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:42.360
it has evolved. 

00:07:42.360 --> 00:07:45.360
It came into existence in WordPress 5.0

00:07:45.360 --> 00:07:49.970
and right now version WordPress 5.5 is running,

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:55.040
and the core Gutenberg plugin gets updated once every two weeks. 

00:07:56.040 --> 00:08:02.040
With every major update 
the core is merged into WordPress core.

00:08:04.440 --> 00:08:09.759
What I have seen is 
there's a collection of blogs, 

00:08:11.759 --> 00:08:17.580
when everyone started talking about Gutenberg
and saying, it's a block-based design.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:20.830
As a person with [a] disability 
I did not understand what is a block. 

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:27.830
So when I was reading articles 
on other blogs and websites

00:08:27.830 --> 00:08:32.389
they said heading block, paragraph block 
or all the list block.

00:08:32.389 --> 00:08:35.430
I did not understand
what is a block.

00:08:35.430 --> 00:08:39.990
Theoretically it was very difficult 
to understand what was a block.

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:43.830
Then when I started working with Gutenberg,

00:08:43.830 --> 00:08:50.830
I got a clear picture that 
every section of the content area

00:08:50.830 --> 00:08:53.690
is called a block. 

00:08:53.690 --> 00:08:57.690
You create a heading,
it is a block on its own.

00:08:57.690 --> 00:09:00.290
You have a paragraph,
it's a block on its own. 

00:09:03.290 --> 00:09:07.290
Gutenberg gives a lot of control 
over the content

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:10.320
and the layout 
of these blocks.

00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:14.779
You can customize the font size, 

00:09:14.779 --> 00:09:20.779
colour and styling. 

00:09:21.779 --> 00:09:25.120
These are some of 
the options that I have seen.

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:27.120
From the technical standpoint,

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.839
for a person with visual disability,

00:09:29.839 --> 00:09:32.839
it was not very useful for me to go and edit,

00:09:32.839 --> 00:09:38.040
because I'm not sure exactly what the
color is going to be on the front end.

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:44.650
Also I generally use the basic 
theme settings that are there.

00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:55.390
We all know the Gutenberg accessibility story – 

00:09:55.390 --> 00:09:57.390
it's merged with 5.0.

00:09:57.390 --> 00:10:01.200
There was a lot of pushback 
from the accessibility community. 

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:07.200
A lot of accessibility professionals

00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:11.870
and the wider community itself said that it
should not be merged with 5.0, 

00:10:12.870 --> 00:10:14.130
because it's not mature.

00:10:15.130 --> 00:10:17.130
There were a lot of 
articles on the web

00:10:17.130 --> 00:10:22.440
where it was told that it was written,

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:28.180
that the design aspect, like accessibility
is not considered from the start. 

00:10:28.180 --> 00:10:34.180
But what I see with a 
two week development cycle

00:10:34.180 --> 00:10:39.709
and being pushed every two weeks,

00:10:39.709 --> 00:10:44.330
it's very difficult to keep up with
accessibility, design, development, and

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:46.300
fixes of accessibility bugs.

00:10:46.300 --> 00:10:51.300
There were a lot of challenges because
there were a lot of moving parts,

00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:54.670
but after two years,

00:10:57.670 --> 00:11:02.650
what happened in 2019 is 
a WP Campus called for 

00:11:02.650 --> 00:11:04.650
an independent audit by an agency.

00:11:04.650 --> 00:11:09.440
The agency provided it results
and we had close to 300 accessibility bugs

00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:13.140
that were found on Gutenberg.

00:11:15.440 --> 00:11:18.140
And the Gutenberg was audited,

00:11:18.140 --> 00:11:22.820
not the plug-in, but the core that
was merged with WordPress. 

00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:28.820
So what did the WP Campus audit show?

00:11:28.820 --> 00:11:32.000
It showed [a] considerable
amount of accessibility bugs.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:35.020
There were more than 300 accessibility bugs.

00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:38.020
Couple [or] more of these bugs were related

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:40.400
to authoring tool where you upload a video

00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:45.400
and there is no way to provide caption.

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:53.690
Some of these are authoring tool challenges
and some are pure accessibility bugs.

00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:57.950
After the WP Campus audit 

00:11:57.950 --> 00:11:59.950
there are a lot of bug fixes on the way.

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:06.800
The accessibility and development teams started
fixing a lot of these accessibility bugs.

00:12:09.800 --> 00:12:13.740
I've personally seen some
of these accessibility fix being in place,

00:12:13.740 --> 00:12:19.589
during the subsequent Gutenberg plugin releases
and in the core merge also.

00:12:19.589 --> 00:12:24.570
If you go to GitHub, 
I provided the link here. 

00:12:24.570 --> 00:12:28.570
There are a couple of significant
accessibility bugs still that are open.

00:12:31.570 --> 00:12:36.360
Some of these bugs are
pure technical related

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:41.540
maybe as a person with disability 
you might not be

00:12:41.540 --> 00:12:46.790
finding it very difficult to navigate,
but they are technically an accessibility bug,

00:12:46.790 --> 00:12:50.019
that's why they are called upon.

00:12:52.019 --> 00:12:58.800
So how is Gutenberg very difficult?

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:03.600
As I said previously,
it's very difficult for screen reader users.

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:10.240
What I did is as a person with a visual disability,

00:13:07.240 --> 00:13:10.899
I work with a lot of other people with disability

00:13:10.240 --> 00:13:16.899
in the local community, so me and couple
of my friends who are all screen reader users

00:13:16.899 --> 00:13:20.690
and some of these people are 
accessibility specialists, 

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:30.959
I gave them... I installed the Gutenberg plug-in

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:31.959
and we, I, studied how they're going to use [it].

00:13:31.959 --> 00:13:35.830
Some of the power screen reader users
found it very difficult.

00:13:35.830 --> 00:13:36.910
They did not understand,

00:13:36.910 --> 00:13:42.360
there are a lot of elements
as soon as you open the post screen,

00:13:42.360 --> 00:13:43.399
add new post screen,

00:13:43.399 --> 00:13:47.050
there are lot of elements.
You click on add block 

00:13:47.050 --> 00:13:49.050
and your focus moves to a search field.

00:13:49.050 --> 00:13:54.270
So they are caught off guard completely.

00:13:55.010 --> 00:13:57.270
We are going to discuss 
some of these during the demo.

00:13:57.270 --> 00:14:00.270
I'll be running a demo of how
I use Gutenberg

00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:06.160
and how it is very different 
from our Classic Editor.

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:11.649
What happens in our Classic Editor is
you have the title screen and the content area

00:14:11.649 --> 00:14:13.630
where you type in the content.

00:14:14.630 --> 00:14:18.110
Or generally what happens 
as a person with disability,  

00:14:18.110 --> 00:14:22.070
we use Microsoft Word and 
we type in our content 

00:14:22.070 --> 00:14:28.070
then we put it in the Classic Editor 
and we use shortcut keys

00:14:28.070 --> 00:14:34.880
to give a heading paragraph and block code 

00:14:34.880 --> 00:14:40.950
and other markup to the content that we created. 

00:14:40.950 --> 00:14:46.370
So it was pretty easy for us 
and some of them said that,

00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:51.640
we know HTML.

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:55.020
So what they do is they use 
the Classic Editor, text mode 

00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:58.020
instead of visual editor 
and they mark up the content

00:14:58.020 --> 00:15:01.680
directly in Microsoft Word and they just put

00:15:01.020 --> 00:15:04.680
it in the editor and publish the content.

00:15:06.680 --> 00:15:10.790
That's where you know as a screen reader user 
it needs a lot of learning curve here.

00:15:13.680 --> 00:15:18.790
It's a lot of visual aspect Gutenberg,
as I said, earlier.

00:15:18.790 --> 00:15:24.029
It's there to create great visual design,

00:15:24.029 --> 00:15:28.200
but as a person with disability 
and who has been writing content 

00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:33.899
for 12–14 years, I did not find it... 

00:15:33.899 --> 00:15:36.899
For me it's just headings, paragraph.

00:15:36.899 --> 00:15:43.180
It's more content than visual aspect of the [unintelligible].

00:15:43.180 --> 00:15:48.660
One of the challenges that we also
faced is with regard to the block definitions.

00:15:49.660 --> 00:15:55.290
Some of the blocks, if you go out
onto the Gutenberg search area 

00:15:55.290 --> 00:15:57.730
and go category by category, 
there are some of these blocks

00:15:57.730 --> 00:16:00.660
like markdown block 
or some of the code

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:04.660
or it's a separator 

00:16:04.660 --> 00:16:07.550
There are some of these blocks 
that we we did not understand,

00:16:07.660 --> 00:16:09.550
what exactly that block does. 

00:16:13.550 --> 00:16:18.519
For some of these blocks 
we were not able to find a definition. 

00:16:18.550 --> 00:16:21.519
So we felt that, if there is a
help what exactly this block does?

00:16:21.519 --> 00:16:24.310
How it is going to show up in the front end?

00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:30.760
It would have been very helpful 
for us to use some of these blocks.

00:16:30.760 --> 00:16:34.720
I'm going to show a demo right now. 

00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:40.300
Robert, I'll be sharing my 
screen reader sound,

00:16:40.720 --> 00:16:46.300
over Zoom so that people 
will be able to hear what I'm navigating.

00:16:51.300 --> 00:16:56.930
<v Roberto> Let me talk with the administrator, 

00:16:56.930 --> 00:17:01.470
because I think what you are 
sharing is your computer sound.

00:17:01.470 --> 00:17:03.610
<v Raghavendra> Yes.

00:17:03.610 --> 00:17:09.770
<v Roberto> Can you place your mic
close to the screen reader?

00:17:09.770 --> 00:17:15.339
<v Raghavendra> [screen reader output] 
Okay, you're able to hear my screen reader?

00:17:15.339 --> 00:17:18.170
<v Roberto> Yes, we hear your screen reader.

00:17:18.170 --> 00:17:24.900
[screen reader reading text] 

00:17:24.900 --> 00:17:27.480
<v Raghavendra> I'm here on a screen.

00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:31.480
This is a post. I created a demo post here.

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:38.000
To get a feel of this particular
page this screen, I use headings. 

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:43.480 
What I'm going to do is I'm going to press 
control home to go to the top of the page

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:46.000
[screen reader output]

00:17:46.480 --> 00:17:47.000
<v Raghavendra> and then

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.240
[screen reader] [unintelligible].... slower
slower slower slower slower.

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:49.290
<v Raghavendra> I'm going to press H.

00:17:49.290 --> 00:17:53.240
[screen reader] Edit post heading level 1,
script setting level 2, status and visibility

00:17:53.240 --> 00:17:58.141
heading level 2 button expanded, permalink
heading level 2 button expanded, view post

00:17:58.141 --> 00:17:59.419
heading level 3,

00:17:59.419 --> 00:18:03.520
categories heading level two button expanded,
tags heading level two button collapsed,

00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:07.710
feature image heading level two button collapsed,
excerpt heading level two button collapsed,

00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:11.520
discussion heading level two button collapsed,
link suggestions heading level two clickable,

00:18:11.520 --> 00:18:13.140
wrapping to top, edit post heading level one.

00:18:13.140 --> 00:18:17.510
<v Raghavendra> I know I'm at the edit post. 
I'm going to press tab here.

00:18:17.510 --> 00:18:21.910
[screen reader] Tab, document tools, toolbars
only, add block toggle button.

00:18:21.910 --> 00:18:27.000
<v Raghavendra> That's a tool bar. As
soon as I hear it's a toolbar, as a person

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:31.590
with screen reader, I know that I had
to use arrow keys to navigate. 

00:18:31.590 --> 00:18:32.590
Let's see what happens.

00:18:32.590 --> 00:18:41.850
[screen reader] Tool, undo button, redo button
available, content structure button collapse,

00:18:41.850 --> 00:18:47.530
block navigation button, add block toggle
button,

00:18:47.530 --> 00:18:51.660
tools button collapsed, to activate press
spacebar, undo button

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:54.330
<v Raghavendra> Let's add a block.

00:18:54.330 --> 00:18:59.200
[screen reader] Add block toggle button enter,
toggle button, press search for a block, block

00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:03.070
library region, search for a block edit, search
for a block, type and text, 110 results found.

00:19:03.070 --> 00:19:04.070
<v Raghavendra> Okay

00:19:04.070 --> 00:19:08.500
[screen reader] Tab, tab, blocks tab, selected
use clause key plus plus m to move the controled

00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:09.500
element, one of three.

00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:13.210
<v Raghavendra> If you see here, there are
three tabs: one is blocks.

00:19:13.210 --> 00:19:14.799
[screen reader] Patterns tab selected styles
...

00:19:14.799 --> 00:19:17.220
<v Raghavendra> These are block patterns.

00:19:17.220 --> 00:19:20.040
[screen reader] Reusable tabs selected used

00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:25.870
<v Raghavendra> And reusable blocks. One
of the one of the things that confused me

00:19:25.870 --> 00:19:28.940
is about this block patterns 
