For most users at the beginning is kind of difficult,

00:34:03.190 --> 00:34:10.210
because there is a lot of stuff to learn. 

00:34:10.210 --> 00:34:13.210
I mean visually it looks very clean and simple

00:34:13.210 --> 00:34:19.269
but I think it's a lot more complicated 
than the regular editor.

00:34:19.269 --> 00:34:28.849
Even at a pro tip when you create content
you can paste all your content 

00:34:28.849 --> 00:34:34.730
on the Classic Editor and then convert 
your Classic Editor into all the different blocks 

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:42.239
and most of the times WordPress will translate all
your different content, but yes it's difficult.

00:34:42.239 --> 00:34:48.429
About the plugins, most of the
plugins are available as a block and then

00:34:48.429 --> 00:34:55.589
you call the plugin, but then you need to
make configurations in the same plugin. 

00:34:55.589 --> 00:35:01.920
So it's very difficult. 
Let's start with the first question:

00:35:01.920 --> 00:35:05.690
Will you find useful to have easy options

00:35:05.690 --> 00:35:14.109
to disable blocks that you can't 
or don't wish to use?

00:35:14.109 --> 00:35:20.410
<v Raghavendra> There are too many block.
I think it's not the question of disabling

00:35:20.410 --> 00:35:28.859
the blocks. I think there are very
few blocks that I use on my websites.

00:35:31.859 --> 00:35:36.349
Sometimes I might use Jetpack,
Eventbrite, the calendar leave block.

00:35:36.349 --> 00:35:45.160
I use them rarely, but I need them. 
So disabling is not an option, 

00:35:45.160 --> 00:35:49.880
but maybe the way I want to approach 
the content itself should be a little different,

00:35:49.880 --> 00:35:57.240
because I don't use all these blocks all
the time and all the options. Robert?

00:35:57.240 --> 00:36:03.720
<v Roberto> Yes sorry, hello over here. 
The next question actually is

00:36:03.720 --> 00:36:09.569
my personal question and is away from
native blocks, because there is a lot of native

00:36:09.569 --> 00:36:16.359
blocks. Did you find the other blocks, the
the plug-in blocks accessible? For example,

00:36:16.359 --> 00:36:23.160
Woo-Commerce, Yoast SEO, other Gravity Forms,
Contact Form 7, stuff that you usually

00:36:23.160 --> 00:36:29.089
use a lot to create content. 
Are they friendly with screen readers or not?

00:36:29.089 --> 00:36:35.109
<v Raghavendra> I'm playing with Woo-Commerce 
right now. Contact Form 7,

00:36:35.109 --> 00:36:40.650
I'm not using it right now, because
I tend to use Jetpack forms. 

00:36:40.650 --> 00:36:48.739
Jetpack forms are very accessible and the Mailchimp block is
accessible. Ranked Math SEO, Yoast SEO and

00:36:48.739 --> 00:36:54.539
other plugins like Atomic Blocks from StudioPress.

00:36:54.539 --> 00:37:04.559
They are accessible – the accordions, the
testimonials block and the author block.

00:37:04.559 --> 00:37:11.009
Most of the blocks I encountered 
are very accessible.

00:37:11.009 --> 00:37:16.499
Creating content has been
very easy inside them.

00:37:16.499 --> 00:37:23.160
<v Roberto> Thank you very much.
The next question will be: 

00:37:23.160 --> 00:37:30.229
Do you find any particular combination 
of screen reader and browser to be better?

00:37:31.229 --> 00:37:37.160
<v Raghavendra> I use JAWS plus Chrome, NVDA
plus Chrome. These are my default screen reader combination.

00:37:41.089 --> 00:37:48.289
I used to use NVDA plus Firefox earlier, but
now I prefer NVDA plus Chrome. 

00:37:48.289 --> 00:37:57.509
It's more supported and 
I learned screen readers using JAWS. 

00:37:57.509 --> 00:38:02.969
It's a very little difficult transition
for me to use full-time N-V-D-A, so I tend

00:38:02.969 --> 00:38:10.359
to use JAWS a lot when I'm not doing accessibility
testing. When I do accessibility testing

00:38:10.359 --> 00:38:17.049
specifically for my clients and or I'm testing
some widget for accessibility I tend to use

00:38:17.049 --> 00:38:20.519
NVDA plus Chrome.

00:38:20.519 --> 00:38:28.549
<v Roberto> Okay thank you, 
the last question is:

00:38:28.549 --> 00:38:37.469
Unexpected changes of focus are one of the
WordPress Accessibility Team common complaints

00:38:37.469 --> 00:38:48.789
about Gutenberg. How often or rarely do you
feel that happen in your users of Gutenberg?

00:38:48.789 --> 00:38:49.979
<v Raghavendra> Robert can you repeat the question?

00:38:49.979 --> 00:38:56.950
<v Robert> So often, the unexpected changes
from one element to another, the focus, 

00:38:56.950 --> 00:39:01.940
is one of the main 
complaints of Gutenberg.

00:39:01.940 --> 00:39:08.059
How often did you think you are 
on one specific place,

00:39:08.059 --> 00:39:13.819
where you want to go to another place
and it's not working properly?

00:39:13.819 --> 00:39:21.219
<v Raghavendra> The major problem that
you run into Gutenberg is because you need

00:39:21.219 --> 00:39:27.790
to understand how this Gutenberg is laid out.
Like being a person with screen reader

00:39:27.790 --> 00:39:34.170
or you can be even a sighted person,
just can't open Gutenberg and understand it

00:39:34.170 --> 00:39:41.950
instantly. Like I run the, I run the Island,
Hyderabad blogging club also here. I run a

00:39:41.950 --> 00:39:47.750
club full of bloggers and most of them, I
think I'm the only person with disability.

00:39:47.750 --> 00:39:51.690
Me and another friend are the only person
with disability in that club and lot of them

00:39:51.690 --> 00:39:55.799
are sighted. And when the Gutenberg came in,
they are like, is there a way to switch back

00:39:55.799 --> 00:39:59.150
to the Classic Editor? 
Is the question they asked.

00:39:59.150 --> 00:40:04.990
We told about the Classic Editor plugin,
but a lot of them did not transition to

00:40:04.990 --> 00:40:09.029
Gutenberg immediately. 
That took a long time to understand.

00:40:09.029 --> 00:40:15.839
We did a lot of workshops with them
to make them understand how Gutenberg works

00:40:15.839 --> 00:40:22.559
and how it helps with the design and all that
and now they fell in love with the Gutenberg.

00:40:22.559 --> 00:40:28.759
They don't want to transition back to Classic
Editor. Because it was so easy for them

00:40:28.759 --> 00:40:35.700
to create stories. It was visual
storytelling and all that. It became

00:40:35.700 --> 00:40:41.049
very easy for them to create, so they don't
want to transition back to the Classic Editor.

00:40:41.049 --> 00:40:47.049
They're using Gutenberg. It takes a lot of
time to learn Gutenberg, that's the only aspect here.

00:40:47.049 --> 00:40:52.209
As a person with a disability 
and a screen reader user,

00:40:52.209 --> 00:40:59.219
it took a lot of time for me to understand
Gutenberg end-to-end. 

00:40:59.219 --> 00:41:03.190
Now I can create blocks, content and all, 
it's just a little difficult for me 

00:41:03.190 --> 00:41:05.190
to manage content rather than create it.

00:41:05.190 --> 00:41:09.170
Like if I have to copy
each paragraph from Word, Microsoft Word and

00:41:09.170 --> 00:41:15.599
put it here into, create one block, put it
in a put it inside that block then go back

00:41:15.599 --> 00:41:21.849
to Word again, come back here put it in heading,
it's taking too much of my time.

00:41:21.849 --> 00:41:31.209
<v Roberto> Awesome, thank you. We
don't have more questions at this moment so

00:41:31.209 --> 00:41:37.160
please the people who is watching this over
YouTube feel free to add your questions into

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:45.239
the YouTube chat and we will answer
that on the presentation.

00:41:45.239 --> 00:41:53.509
Meantime, maybe I have a last question because
we have another two minutes.

00:41:53.509 --> 00:42:01.539
What what do you recommend for people
who is blind or have a disability, to

00:42:01.539 --> 00:42:04.010
interact directly with Gutenberg?

00:42:04.010 --> 00:42:10.940
You already say it take a lot of time, not
just to understand how Gutenberg work, but

00:42:10.940 --> 00:42:14.940
to create great content beyond 
the tips that you already give.

00:42:14.940 --> 00:42:21.089
Create your content on a Word document and
paste it into WordPress. 

00:42:21.089 --> 00:42:26.510
What other kind of tip do you have for people?

00:42:26.510 --> 00:42:32.710
<v Raghavendra> So one of the other things is,
as you said earlier what I do is create

00:42:32.710 --> 00:42:37.900
the content, put it in the Classic Block,
Classic Editor, then I use this plugin called

00:42:37.900 --> 00:42:48.940
I think, Bulk Gutenberg, so you change all
the posts into blocks.

00:42:48.940 --> 00:42:59.979
So I converted old posts and new posts.
I put them as a regular Classic Block and

00:42:59.979 --> 00:43:06.459
then I convert them into blocks. So what I
also did is right now I had a virtual assistant

00:43:06.459 --> 00:43:14.599
who is helping me with, who's a sighted person
helping me with all the visual aspect of the

00:43:14.599 --> 00:43:21.400
design aspect. Like I only concentrate on
the content and they take care of the pictures,

00:43:21.400 --> 00:43:24.269
the visual aspect of all the other things.

00:43:24.269 --> 00:43:29.829
[Roberto] Okay, awesome thank you. And maybe
the the last question, because we don't get

00:43:29.829 --> 00:43:37.040
any other ones and I have always questions: 
If you run as a lead of the WordPress project at this moment

00:43:37.040 --> 00:43:41.529
and you decide let's do this 100 percent accessible,

00:43:41.529 --> 00:43:47.750
where did you focus to make Gutenberg and
this experience more accessible? 

00:43:47.750 --> 00:43:53.680
What do you want to see on the future or what do you want
to see on Gutenberg to be more accessible?

00:43:53.680 --> 00:43:59.599
<v Raghavendra> If you ask me like what I am
thinking is as I said, uh I want to create

00:43:59.599 --> 00:44:04.180
content in Microsoft Word.
Just come here put it and then work on the

00:44:04.180 --> 00:44:11.150
formatting and then maybe you know a button
or uh option where it will convert everything

00:44:11.150 --> 00:44:14.019
into blocks. And then I hand over
it to my design team.

00:44:14.019 --> 00:44:22.589
Basically, I come from the content aspect
of this and as a person with the visual disability,

00:44:22.589 --> 00:44:26.529
I don't know if I insert a picture, 
where I'm inserting it,

00:44:26.529 --> 00:44:34.780
or is it taking completely over 
what is the cropping of the image,

00:44:37.380 --> 00:44:42.529
where it is placed. Is it placed to the left
or right, all that aspect. So I normally tend

00:44:42.529 --> 00:44:49.579
to leave all the design decisions to the design
team and then just work on the content aspect.

00:44:49.579 --> 00:44:55.959
If you ask me right now what I
would want to see is, I just want to see

00:44:55.959 --> 00:45:01.930
how this Classic Block is there right
now, if I want to input the content I want

00:45:01.930 --> 00:45:08.779
to input here, format it, then a button or
you know an option just to convert everything

00:45:08.779 --> 00:45:15.990
into blocks. And then the design
team can take it forward from there.

00:45:15.990 --> 00:45:24.010
It should be easy for me to publish content,
format content, edit content also. 

00:45:24.010 --> 00:45:29.269
One of the main challenges that we are facing
right now is with the editing of the content.

00:45:30.269 --> 00:45:37.759
Once we put all the content into blocks, 
editing of the content is becoming very difficult.

00:45:40.759 --> 00:45:42.400
Like you want to edit a 
certain line in a particular paragraph,

00:45:43.400 --> 00:45:47.030
we used to copy all the content into

00:45:48.030 --> 00:45:52.789
Microsoft Word from the Classic Editor do
Control F, look for that particular keyword

00:45:53.789 --> 00:45:59.609
and wherever we are supposed to edit them
and just put it back into the editor.

00:45:59.609 --> 00:46:07.680
But now with the Gutenberg, it's it's like
you know I have four paragraphs, four headings,

00:46:07.680 --> 00:46:14.410
couple of lists, uh it became very difficult
for us to edit the content. And if I copy

00:46:14.410 --> 00:46:20.059
from the Code Editor, all the HTML code also
comes in. So it's just not really working

00:46:20.059 --> 00:46:25.719
out. It should become easy for us 
to edit content in Gutenberg.

00:46:25.719 --> 00:46:31.790
<v Roberto> Awesome, well thank you very much. Great.

00:46:31.790 --> 00:46:42.720
This talk, you have been amazing.
I think that's all for tonight guys. 

00:46:42.720 --> 00:46:50.719
Please let's thank Raghavendra and let's remember we
we're gonna have our next talk on possibly

00:46:50.719 --> 00:46:54.130
10 minutes, 6 UTC time.

00:46:54.130 --> 00:47:00.200
It will be Accessibility by Default
in Authoring Tools by Susanna Laurin. 

00:47:00.200 --> 00:47:06.509
It will be on the same channel. 

00:47:06.509 --> 00:47:10.140
Let's gonna take a little break and 
we will see you again soon. Bye.

00:47:10.140 --> 00:47:15.449
<v Raghavendra> Thank you, thank you everyone.
I'll be updating my presentation and 

00:47:15.449 --> 00:47:23.309
give it to the team here and you can all
follow me on Twitter and other accessible,

00:47:23.309 --> 00:47:24.529
all the other channels.
